title: @OspreyWSOC Blanks NJIT 3-0 Friday in A-Sun Action
text: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€“ The North Florida women's soccer team earned their second straight A-Sun win, defeating NJIT 3-0 Friday night at Hodges Stadium. The Ospreys (4-8-0, 2-1-0 A-Sun) now sit in third place in the conference standings behind Lipscomb and FGCU. "We had a really good week of training and we wanted to build off of the momentum of last week's win over Stetson. We worked a lot on possession and keeping the ball plus some attacking themes," said coach . "We knew we had two tough games this weekend and wanted to come out tonight and get a result. Now we focus on Lipscomb on Sunday."
